Defendant Kathren L Douglas in court with attorney Victor E Plantinga.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin assisted by Atty. Bruan Juech.
Sentencing argument by Intern Lucas Bennewitz and Atty. Plantinga.  Statement by defendant's mother and by defendant.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed Sentence of:

54 months  Imprisonment (Credit - 1 day )
- 18 months  of Initial Confinement
- 36 months  of Extended Supervision

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Mental Health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Perform  10 hours of community service each year of extended supervision;
- Be involved in 12 step program with 30 days and obtain a mentor/sponsor within 45 days;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
-Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge

BUY MONEY: $300.00 to be paid during extended supervison joint and several with co-defendent

Costs: $268.00 BAIL TO APPLY
DNA Surcharge:  $250.00  BAIL TO APPLY
DNA Sample ordered.
(To be paid during 1st 6 months of extended supervision.)

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program
